SIMPLE: traverser
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Traverser
<hw>Trav"ers*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who, or that which, traverses, or moves, as an index on a scale, and the
like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>One who traverses, or
denies.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Railroad)</fld> <def>A traverse table. See under
<er>Traverse</er>, <pos>n.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Traversing</ent>⟦br⟧
